    "pathophysiology": "Deletion or mutation of alpha-globin genes on chromosome 16 leads to reduced or absent alpha-globin chain synthesis. The excess beta chains (in older children/adults) or gamma chains (in neonates) form unstable tetramers (HbH or Hb Bart) that precipitate within RBCs, causing premature destruction (hemolysis) and ineffective erythropoiesis. Severity correlates with the number of deleted genes: 4-gene deletion (Hb Bart hydrops fetalis) is incompatible with life, 3-gene deletion (HbH disease) causes moderate hemolytic anemia, 2-gene deletion (alpha-thal trait) causes microcytosis without significant anemia, and 1-gene deletion (silent carrier) is clinically silent.",
